			<h1 id="link1">General Questions</h1>
		  <h3>What is Research Nation?</h3>
		  <p>Research Nation is an online marketplace for market research</p>
		  <h3>What's different about it?</h3>
		  <p>All content is user-generated and limited in length (5 pages maximum), and everything we put on the site is reviewed, rated, and fully curated.</p>
		  <h3>How do you select buyers?</h3>
		  <p>Anyone is free to buy research on the site. Most research will be for less than US$100, which means that it will be affordable to individuals and small businesses.</p>
		  <h3>How do you guarantee quality?</h3>
		  <p>Quality is very important to us and we ensure it through a couple of checks. First, we read, edit and review every single file that is uploaded onto our site. If something doesn't meet our quality standards, it won't be allowed. Second, we rate each review and the good ones will be given a  koala standard stamp of approval. Finally, every report comes with user reviews (powered through Facebook, so minimal spam), so you know what others think of the report.</p>
		  <h3>Is it legal?</h3>
		  <p>Yes, it is. We only allow original work on our site. No re-selling is allowed. In order to ensure that the files we get are original work, we ask that they be submitted in editable format – that is Excel, PowerPoint or Word.</p>
		  <h3>How do you make money?</h3>
		  <p>We make money by charging a commission on every document that is sold. This commission is 30%. </p>
		  <h3>Who's on your team?</h3>
		  <p>Koala Faisal, Baby Samreen and Koala with Four Arms, Ali.</p>
		  <h3>Why are you doing this?</h3>
		  <p>We're doing this because we're sick of paying thousands of dollars for market research that is no good. It's an industry that is just begging to be shaken up and democratized. By unlocking the power of intelligent minds on the internet – giving them a way to publish, be recognized and make money – we're hoping we can make some of the suits on Madison Avenue wake up and sweat it out a little bit.</p>
		  <h3>How do you protect my privacy?</h3>
		  <p>We realize this is a concern for you. Your data will always be your data, and there's no koala in the world that can change that. If you want to delete a post, you can do so in the manage section. If you want to delete your account altogether, just email us at admin@researchnation.net, and we'll get it done and send you a confirmation. Finally, rest assured we we will never share your information with anyone else without your permission.</p>
